 the project. For now, it is just a placeholder!","lastModifiedDate":"2026-03-03T14:32:26","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":10,"author":{"gitId":"henghengyh"},"content":"","lastModifiedDate":"2026-03-03T14:32:26","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":11,"author":{"gitId":"henghengyh"},"content":"AddressBook - Level 3 is a desktop address book application used for teaching Software Engineering principles. The user interacts with it using a CLI, and it has a GUI created with JavaFX. It is written in Java, and has about 10 kLoC.","lastModifiedDate":"2026-03-03T14:32:26","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":12,"author":{"gitId":"henghengyh"},"content":"","lastModifiedDate":"2026-03-03T14:32:26","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":13,"author":{"gitId":"henghengyh"},"content":"Given below are my contributions to the project.","lastModifiedDate":"2026-03-03T14:32:26","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":14,"author":{"gitId":"henghengyh"},"content":"","lastModifiedDate":"2026-03-03T14:32:26","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":15,"author":{"gitId":"henghengyh"},"content":"* **New Feature**: Added the ability to undo/redo previous commands.","lastModifiedDate":"2026-03-03T14:32:26","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":16,"author":{"gitId":"henghengyh"},"content":"  * What it does: allows the user to undo all previous commands one at a time. Preceding undo commands can be reversed by using the redo command.","lastModifiedDate":"2026-03-03T14:32:26","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":17,"author":{"gitId":"henghengyh"},"content":"  * Justification: This feature improves the product significantly because a user can make mistakes in commands and the app should provide a convenient way to rectify them.","lastModifiedDate":"2026-03-03T14:32:26","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":18,"author":{"gitId":"henghengyh"},"content":"  * Highlights: This enhancement affects existing commands and commands to be added in future. It required an in-depth analysis of design alternatives. The implementation too was challenging as it required changes to existing commands.","lastModifiedDate":"2026-03-03T14:32:26","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":19,"author":{"gitId":"henghengyh"},"content":"  * Credits: *{mention here if you reused any code/ideas from elsewhere or if a third-party library is heavily used in the feature so that a reader can make a more accurate judgement of how much effort went into the feature}*","lastModifiedDate":"2026-03-03T14:32:26","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":20,"author":{"gitId":"henghengyh"},"content":"","lastModifiedDate":"2026-03-03T14:32:26","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":21,"author":{"gitId":"henghengyh"},"content":"* **New Feature**: Added a history command that allows the user to navigate to previous commands using up/down keys.","lastModifiedDate":"2026-03-03T14:32:26","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":22,"author":{"gitId":"henghengyh"},"content":"","lastModifiedDate":"2026-03-03T14:32:26","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":23,"author":{"gitId":"henghengyh"},"content":"* **Code contributed**: [RepoSense link]()","lastModifiedDate":"2026-03-03T14:32:26","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":24,"author":{"gitId":"henghengyh"},"content":"","lastModifiedDate":"2026-03-03T14:32:26","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":25,"author":{"gitId":"henghengyh"},"content":"* **Project management**:","lastModifiedDate":"2026-03-03T14:32:26","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":26,"author":{"gitId":"henghengyh"},"content":"  * Managed releases `v1.3` - `v1.5rc` (3 releases) on GitHub","lastModifiedDate":"2026-03-03T14:32:26","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":27,"author":{"gitId":"henghengyh"},"content":"","lastModifiedDate":"2026-03-03T14:32:26","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":28,"author":{"gitId":"henghengyh"},"content":"* **Enhancements to existing features**:","lastModifiedDate":"2026-03-03T14:32:26","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":29,"author":{"gitId":"henghengyh"},"content":"  * Updated the GUI color scheme (Pull requests [\\#33](), [\\#34]())","lastModifiedDate":"2026-03-03T14:32:26","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":30,"author":{"gitId":"henghengyh"},"content":"  * Wrote additional tests for existing features to increase coverage from 88% to 92% (Pull requests [\\#36](), [\\#38]())","lastModifiedDate":"2026-03-03T14:32:26","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":31,"author":{"gitId":"henghengyh"},"content":"","lastModifiedDate":"2026-03-03T14:32:26","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":32,"author":{"gitId":"henghengyh"},"content":"* **Documentation**:","lastModifiedDate":"2026-03-03T14:32:26","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":33,"author":{"gitId":"henghengyh"},"content":"  * User Guide:","lastModifiedDate":"2026-03-03T14:32:26","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":34,"author":{"gitId":"henghengyh"},"content":"    * Added documentation for the features `delete` and `find` [\\#72]()","lastModifiedDate":"2026-03-03T14:32:26","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":35,"author":{"gitId":"henghengyh"},"content":"    * Did cosmetic tweaks to existing documentation of features `clear`, `exit`: [\\#74]()","lastModifiedDate":"2026-03-03T14:32:26","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":36,"author":{"gitId":"henghengyh"},"content":"  * Developer Guide:","lastModifiedDate":"2026-03-03T14:32:26","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":37,"author":{"gitId":"henghengyh"},"content":"    * Added implementation details of the `delete` feature.","lastModifiedDate":"2026-03-03T14:32:26","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":38,"author":{"gitId":"henghengyh"},"content":"","lastModifiedDate":"2026-03-03T14:32:26","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":39,"author":{"gitId":"henghengyh"},"content":"* **Community**:","lastModifiedDate":"2026-03-03T14:32:26","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":40,"author":{"gitId":"henghengyh"},"content":"  * PRs reviewed (with non-trivial review comments): [\\#12](), [\\#32](), [\\#19](), [\\#42]()","lastModifiedDate":"2026-03-03T14:32:26","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":41,"autho